{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Amphitheatre Glacier | other_name = | photo = | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Amphitheatre Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = moraine covered | location = [[Victoria Land]] | coordinates = {{coord|78|17|S|163|4|E|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = | width = | thickness = | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Roaring Valley]] | status = | embedded = }}
'''Amphitheatre Glacier''' ({{Coord|78|17|S|163|4|E|display=inline,title}}) is a [[moraine]]-covered [[glacier]] that flows north from [[The Amphitheatre]] into [[Roaring Valley]], in the [[Royal Society Range]] of [[Antarctica]]. It was named by a [[New Zealand Geographical Society]] field party in the area, 1977&ndash;78, in association with The Amphitheatre.
