{{about|the crater on Mars|the crater on the Moon|Arago (lunar crater)}} {{Infobox Mars crater | name = Arago Crater | image = Wikigillmap.jpg | image_size = 450px | caption = MOLA map, showing Arago crater and other nearby craters. Colors indicate elevations, Arago is mapped on the lower right end. | region = [[Arabia quadrangle]] | coordinates = {{coord|10.22|N|29.93|E|globe:mars_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | discoverer = | diameter = 152 km | eponym = [[François Arago]] }}
'''Arago''' is a small impact crater in the [[Arabia quadrangle]] on Mars at 10.22 N and 29.93° E. and is 152&nbsp;km in diameter and is in the northernmost of [[Terra Sabaea]]. Its name was approved in 1973 and is named after the French astronomer [[François Arago]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature {{!}} Arago|url=http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/338|website=usgs.gov|publisher=[[International Astronomical Union]]|accessdate=20 August 2017}}</ref> Most of the crater is flat.
Nearby named prominent craters include [[Cassini (Martian crater)|Cassini]] to the north, the large [[Tikhonravov (crater)|Tikhonravov]] to the east, [[Janssen (Martian crater)|Janssen]] to the southeast, Tuscaloosa to the south, [[Henry (Martian crater)|Henry]] to the west and [[Pasteur (Martian crater)|Pasteur]] to the north-northwest.
Just south of the crater rim is [[Naktong Vallis]] and north of the crater is [[Scamander Vallis]].
==Gallery== <gallery class="center" widths="350px" heights="300px" > Image:Arabia map.JPG|Map of [[Arabia quadrangle]] with major craters. Arago is between Henry and Tikhonravev but the name is not shown </gallery>
