{{Infobox telescope}}
'''EMBRACE''' ('''E'''lectronic '''M'''ulti'''B'''eam '''R'''adio '''A'''stronomy '''C'''onc'''E'''pt) is a prototype telescope for the phase 2 of the [[Square Kilometre Array]] (SKA) project. It's the first dense phased array for radioastronomy in the GHz frequency range (initially planned for covering the 0.5-1.5&nbsp;GHz, mid-frequency band of SKA). It is composed of two sites, one at the [[Nançay radio telescope]] station in France, and one near the [[Westerbork Synthesis Radio Telescope]] antennas in Netherlands.

